All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Algorithm
Abstract class used for instanciating objects that solve the problem.
ComputerLab
Class containing the representation of the Computer Laboratories.
DSaturAlgorithm
Class containting state information needed to solve solution via DSatur Algorithm, filling Solution object with Room objects suitable for every Eveniment object in the Problem object.
Eveniment
Class containting the representation of an event, encapsulating state information needed for operations done in choosing the best Eventiment for the best Room.
EventsComparator
Class that implements interface Comparator.
GreedyAlgorithm
Class used to solve a Problem using greedy manner The state of the class is represented by the Problem itself, which is manipulated so it can produce a Solution object.
LectureHall
Class containing the representation of the Lecture Rooms.
Main
Class used to show the example presented at the 2nd Laboratory and the random tests for Bonus part(to be implemented).
NodeInfo
Record used to keep together information about the saturation degree of an object, its degree in the remaining graph after choosing some objects and index of the event that is tried to be matched with a room.
NodesComparator
Class that implements interface Comparator.
Problem
Class containing the representation of the problem, being able to manipulate Event and Room objects, such that the problem can be solved optimally.
RandomTestsGenerator
Class containting the data needed to generate random big tests, filling Problem object with Eveniment and Room objects.
Room
Abstract Class containing the representation of the Rooms.
RoomsComparator
Class that implements interface Comparator.
Solution
Class containting the representation of an event, encapsulating state information needed for operations done in choosing the best Eventiment for the best Room.
